      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SPRINGER'S BOY (8) is an honest type in the frame at 19 of 39 starts including last time when second (25.52) over 450m at Warrnambool. Performs well off this draw. Drawn out but with clear running expected to go close. PAW ENSLEY (1) was out of character last run when missing the frame, finishing seventh (23.10) in a Grade 4/5 at this track. Generally fast into stride but was shuffled back from the tricky draw last time. Has a strong winning record here at this journey. Has a strong record from box 1, including two wins. Should be about the money. UBIQUITOUS (3) had won two in a row before finishing seventh (22.55) last time at Shepparton. Form at the trip sound including nine wins. Deserves plenty of respect. MR. KIA ORA (7) has been freshened and can sneak into the frame on his best form.",
